doc.after: Since the Neolithic period the native inhabitants of the Lithuanian territory have not been replaced by any other ethnic group so there is a high probability that the inhabitants of present day Lithuania have preserved the genetic composition of their forebears relatively undisturbed by the major demographic movements 67 although without being actually isolated from them 68 The Lithuanian population appears to be relatively homogeneous without apparent genetic differences among ethnic subgroups 69
